                            <comment id="17458486" author="JIRAUSER281726" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2021 15:37:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While trying to create an MCVE, I couldn&#8217;t reproduce the issue I had in my application.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&#8217;ll investigate further what happened in my application, but for now I&#8217;m closing this as invalid. Sorry.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17458724" author="vy" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2021 21:18:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=EtienneMiret&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;EtienneMiret&quot;&gt;EtienneMiret&lt;/a&gt;, in these&#160;occasions, a test reproducing the issue will be greatly appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17460627" author="JIRAUSER281726" created="Thu, 16 Dec 2021 11:08:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vy&quot;&gt;vy&lt;/a&gt; yes, of course. But when I tried to reproduce this issue in a minimal project, the &lt;tt&gt;ContextSelector&lt;/tt&gt; inside the &lt;tt&gt;Log4jContextFactory&lt;/tt&gt; was a &lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ClassLoaderContextSelector&lt;/tt&gt;, which supports a null entry in its &lt;tt&gt;getContext&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;tt&gt;(&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;String&lt;/font&gt;,&lt;font color=&quot;#0033b3&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;ClassLoader&lt;/font&gt;, &lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Map&lt;/font&gt;.&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Entry&lt;/font&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;String&lt;/font&gt;, &lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/font&gt;&amp;gt;, &lt;font color=&quot;#0033b3&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/font&gt;, &lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;URI&lt;/font&gt;)&lt;/tt&gt; method. In my application, for a reason I couldn&#8217;t point, I ended up with a &lt;tt&gt;BasicContextSelector&lt;/tt&gt; which, well, doesn&#8217;t.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
